The paper deals with low-shot learning and image recognition, which are topics commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed approach involves capturing deep encoded distance metrics, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as similarity learning, which is a topic studied in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
